<exercise id="fs-id1171470886351">
<problem id="fs-id1171471054219">
<para id="fs-id1171471021347">Why were the early U.S. political parties formed?</para>
</problem>
<solution id="fs-id1171471110269">
<para id="fs-id1171470926448">Early parties were electoral coalitions of elites, mostly in the U.S. Congress. They were mostly designed to help win House elections and the presidency, but they quickly expanded activities to the state level.</para>
</solution>
</exercise>
